        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 1:48PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 147 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles southeast of McCamey, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Best and Rankin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
